    faithJourney:
      "Eutychus's faith journey is unlike anyone else's in Scripture because his defining moment happened while he was unconscious. He didn't choose to fall. He didn't demonstrate great faith or great doubt. He was a young man in a crowded room who lost the battle with sleep, and the rest of his story was written by gravity and grace. His experience of death and resurrection was entirely passive — something done to him, then something done for him.\n\nBut that passivity is itself a kind of testimony. Not every encounter with God is initiated by the person. Not every spiritual turning point comes from a decision, a prayer, or a crisis of conscience. Sometimes grace shows up while you're unconscious, and you wake up to discover that you've been carried through something you had no power to survive. Eutychus went home alive, and the text says the community was deeply comforted — not just relieved. His survival mattered to the people around him, which means his life had weight in that community even before it became a miracle story. He was worth raising, and he didn't have to earn it.",
